🐍 Snake Game
A simple and interactive Snake Game implemented in Python using the Turtle Graphics Library. The player controls the snake, eats food to grow longer, and avoids collisions with walls or its own body.

🎮 Gameplay Instructions
Controls: Use the arrow keys to move the snake:
⬆️ Up
⬇️ Down
⬅️ Left
➡️ Right

Objective:
Eat food to grow longer and increase your score.
Avoid running into the walls or yourself.
Game Over: The game ends if the snake collides with the walls or its own body.

🛠 Features
Smooth and responsive movement using the Turtle library.
Snake grows dynamically after eating food.
Real-time score tracking.
Simple, modular, and beginner-friendly code structure.

📋 Requirements
Make sure you have Python 3.x installed. The game uses the following standard library:
turtle

🚀 How to Run the Game
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/prakirtibista/Snake_Game.git
Navigate to the project directory:
cd Snake_Game
Run the game:
python snake_game.py


